From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 15:16:36 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] power: domain: add a Rockchip RK3576 PMU power-domain driver

Minimal PMU power-domain driver for the RK3576: power a domain up or
down via the PMU gate, then always de-assert the idle request, wait for
the ack, and ungate the fabric clocks - including when the domain
already reads as powered, so on() is idempotent and a domain left
half-configured by an earlier boot stage still gets de-idled. The
display stack uses it for PD_VO0.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig           |   2 +
 drivers/power/domain/Kconfig               |   9 +
 drivers/power/domain/Makefile              |   1 +
 drivers/power/domain/rk3576-power-domain.c | 184 +++++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 196 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/power/domain/rk3576-power-domain.c

